      "parameters": {
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=You are a combo deal planner for a Danish supermarket reducing food waste.\n\nSTRICT RULES:\n- ONLY use products from the list below. Never invent or add any product not in this list.\n- ONLY use food products. Never include cleaning products, household items, or non-food items.\n- Each product can only appear in ONE combo. Once used, do not reuse it in another combo.\n- Each combo must make real culinary sense for any meal occasion (breakfast, lunch, dinner, snack, brunch etc).\n- Each combo must have between 2 and 4 products.\n- Always prioritise products with the FEWEST days left first.\n- Discount is the AVERAGE of all products' urgency discounts in the combo, rounded to nearest 10%.\n\nUrgency discount rules per product:\n- 0–1 days left = 40%\n- 2–3 days left = 30%\n- 4–5 days left = 20%\n- 6–7 days left = 10%\n\nNear-expiry products (sorted by urgency):\n{{ $json.data.sort((a,b) => a['Days to Expiry'] - b['Days to Expiry']).filter(p => !['Cleaning','Household','Personal Care'].includes(p['Category'])).map(p => `- ${p['Product Name']} | Category: ${p['Category']} | Days left: ${p['Days to Expiry']} | Stock: ${p['Stock Qty']} | Price: ${p['Selling Price']} DKK`).join('\\n') }}\n\nGenerate exactly 5 combo deals using ONLY the products above. Each product must appear in only one combo.\n\nUse this EXACT format for each combo, no extra text:\n\nCOMBO 1\nCOMBO_NAME: [meal name]\nPRODUCTS: [product1], [product2], [product3]\nDAYS_LEFT: [days left of most urgent product]\nURGENCY: [Critical / Soon / Moderate]\nDISCOUNT: [X]%\nORIGINAL_PRICE: [X.XX]\nFINAL_PRICE: [X.XX]\nSAVINGS: [X.XX]\nSTOCK: [stock qty of each product separated by commas]\nMAX_COMBOS: [minimum stock quantity among all products in this combo]\nMEAL_OCCASION: [e.g. Quick Dinner, Weekend Brunch, Family Lunch]\nACTION: [e.g. Promote today, Place near checkout, Add to app deal]\n\nCOMBO 2\n...\n\nCOMBO 3\n...\n\nCOMBO 4\n...\n\nCOMBO 5\n...",
        "options": {}
      },
